  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Sleep Apnea Syndrome (SAS) is highly prevalent in acute stroke and it is related to worst&#xD;
      outcome. We aim to assess if SAS treatment, started immediately after acute ischemic stroke,&#xD;
      impacts infarct growing and clinical prognosis.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <overall_status>Not yet recruiting</overall_status>
